{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.22",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 22 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Themanite answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:2",
      "text": "Can man be compared with God, even though he were of perfect knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:3",
      "text": "What doth it profit God if thou be just? or what dost thou give him if thy way be unspotted?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:4",
      "text": "Shall he reprove thee for fear, and come with thee into judgment:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:5",
      "text": "And not for thy manifold wickedness and thy infinite iniquities?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:6",
      "text": "For thou hast taken away the pledge of thy brethren without cause, and stripped them naked of their clothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:7",
      "text": "Thou hast not given water to the weary, thou hast withdrawn bread from the hungry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:8",
      "text": "In the strength of thy arm thou didst possess the land, and being the most mighty thou holdest it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:9",
      "text": "Thou hast sent widows away empty, and the arms of the fatherless thou hast broken in pieces.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:10",
      "text": "Therefore art thou surrounded with snares, and sudden fear troubleth thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:11",
      "text": "And didst thou think that thou shouldst not see darkness, and that thou shouldst not be covered with the violence of overflowing waters?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:12",
      "text": "Dost not thou think that God is higher than heaven, and is elevated above the height of the stars?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:13",
      "text": "And thou sayst: What doth God know? and he judgeth as it were through a mist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:14",
      "text": "The clouds are his covert, and he doth not consider our things, and he walketh about the poles of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:15",
      "text": "Dost thou desire to keep the path of ages, which wicked men have spurned?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:16",
      "text": "Who were taken away before their time, and a flood hath overthrown their foundation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:17",
      "text": "Who said to God: Depart from us: and looked upon the Almighty as if he could do nothing:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:18",
      "text": "Whereas he had filled their houses with good things: whose way of thinking be far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:19",
      "text": "The just shall see, and shall rejoice, and the innocent shall laugh them to scorn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:20",
      "text": "Is not their exaltation cut down, and hath not fire devoured the remnants of them?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:21",
      "text": "Submit thyself then to him, and be at peace: and thereby thou shalt have the best fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:22",
      "text": "Receive the law of his mouth, and lay up his words in thy heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:23",
      "text": "If thou wilt return to the Almighty, thou shalt be built up, and shalt put away iniquity far from thy tabernacle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:24",
      "text": "He shall give for earth flint, and for flint torrents of gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:25",
      "text": "And the Almighty shall be against thy enemies, and silver shall be heaped together for thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:26",
      "text": "Then shalt thou abound in delights in the Almighty, and shalt lift up thy face to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:27",
      "text": "Thou shalt pray to him, and he will hear thee, and thou shalt pay vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:28",
      "text": "Thou shalt decree a thing, and it shall come to thee, and light shall shine in thy ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:29",
      "text": "For he that hath been humbled, shall be in glory: and he that shall bow down his eyes, he shall be saved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.22.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 22:30",
      "text": "The innocent shall be saved, and he shall be saved by the cleanness of his hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
